iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Mogadishu - A police officer says a suicide car bomber has detonated near a hotel in Somalia's capital, killing at least six people and injuring four others.Captain Mohamed Hussein says the bomber detonated near the Weheliye hotel on the busy Maka Almukarramah road on Monday morning.Ambulances have rushed to the scene.There has been no immediate claim of responsibility for the blast. However, the al-Qaeda-linked Islamic extremist group al-Shabaab often carries out such attacks.Despite being ousted from most of its key strongholds in south and central Somalia, the extremist group continues to carry out deadly guerrilla attacks across the country.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.